      "explained": "Learners produced a complete, evidence-based final explanation of why the Kericho farmer's heart attack affected his whole body: the blocked coronary artery starved the heart muscle of oxygen, reducing cardiac output; less oxygenated blood reached all organs and tissues; deoxygenated haemoglobin in peripheral blood vessels caused the blue lips (cyanosis); the heart attempted to compensate by beating faster; and years of a diet high in saturated fat and physical labour under high cardiovascular stress had progressively narrowed his coronary arteries through atherosclerotic plaque accumulation — all of which could have been slowed or prevented through dietary changes and regular health monitoring."
