  "instructions": "This is your Final Explanation assessment for Sub-strand 3.2: Transport in Animals. You have spent eight lessons building your understanding of how the circulatory system works, starting from the case of the Kericho maize farmer who collapsed while carrying a heavy load uphill. In this assessment, you will use everything you have learned to construct a full scientific explanation of why a blocked coronary artery affected the farmer's entire body. Answer each section thoroughly, using correct biological vocabulary and referring to Kenyan contexts where possible. Write in full sentences and organise your ideas clearly. You will be assessed on the accuracy of your biological knowledge, the quality of your reasoning, and your ability to connect different parts of the circulatory system into one coherent explanation. This is an individual task. Read each prompt carefully before writing your response.",
